It's great to read all this. Well done!
I'm soon in a similar situation. I'll need a new website and am working on a list of what I'd like for accessibility and data protection (no Google Analytics, etc.), and I'm trying to figure out how to make Signal my standard for video calls. It's definitely going to be a lot of work to explain it to customers, but I think it's worth it!
You're doing great, and I'd be happy to help you with my own experiences.
Website: Take a look at @user5. It seems simple, looks great, and is OpenSource. I'll be switching one of my websites to it before the next renewal.
Signal: Take a look at cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service with integrations that allow you to plan video calls with Element Call, Jitsi, etc. Signal is also supported, but I haven't tried it out yet to see if it works for messages or video.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, open source.
